00036  * lustre/utils/ll_decode_filter_fid.c
00037  *
00038  * Tool for printing the OST filter_fid structure on the objects
00039  * in human readable form.
00040  *
00041  * Author: Andreas Dilger <adilger@sun.com>
00042  */
00043 
00044 
00045 #include <stdio.h>
00046 #include <errno.h>
00047 #include <sys/types.h>
00048 #include <sys/xattr.h>
00049 #include <libcfs/byteorder.h>
00050 #include <lustre/lustre_user.h>
00051 
00052 int main(int argc, char *argv[])
00053 {
00054         int rc = 0;
00055         int i;
00056 
00057         for (i = 1; i < argc; i++) {
00058                 char buf[1024]; /* allow xattr that may be larger */
00059                 struct filter_fid *ff = (void *)buf;
00060                 int size;
00061 
00062                 size = getxattr(argv[i], "trusted.fid", buf,
00063                                 sizeof(struct filter_fid_old));
00064                 if (size < 0) {
00065                         fprintf(stderr, "%s: error reading fid: %s\n",
00066                                 argv[i], strerror(errno));
00067                         if (rc == 0)
00068                                 rc = size;
00069                         continue;
00070                 }
00071                 if (size > sizeof(struct filter_fid_old)) {
00072                         fprintf(stderr, "%s: warning: fid larger than expected"
00073                                 " (%d bytes), recompile?\n", argv[i], size);
00074                 } else if (size > sizeof(*ff)) {
00075                         struct filter_fid_old *ffo = (void *)buf;
00076 
00077                         /* old filter_fid */
00078                         printf("%s: objid=%llu seq=%llu parent="DFID
00079                                " stripe=%u\n", argv[i],
00080                                (unsigned long long)le64_to_cpu(ffo->ff_objid),
00081                                (unsigned long long)le64_to_cpu(ffo->ff_seq),
00082                                (unsigned long long)le64_to_cpu(ffo->ff_parent.f_seq),
00083                                le32_to_cpu(ffo->ff_parent.f_oid), 0 /* ver */,
00084                                /* this is stripe_nr actually */
00085                                le32_to_cpu(ffo->ff_parent.f_stripe_idx));
00086                 } else {
00087                         printf("%s: parent="DFID" stripe=%u\n", argv[i],
00088                                (unsigned long long)le64_to_cpu(ff->ff_parent.f_seq),
00089                                le32_to_cpu(ff->ff_parent.f_oid), 0, /* ver */
00090                                /* this is stripe_nr actually */
00091                                le32_to_cpu(ff->ff_parent.f_stripe_idx));
00092                 }
00093         }
00094 
00095         return rc;
00096 }
